<div class='margins story-body'>
    <p class="body-text">Places of worship have been the number one target for the past three years for unknown attackers, likely because of a growing white nationalism movement in the U.S. that has divided the country.</p>
    <p class='body-text'>For 2015, the most popular motive recorded by START speculates the attacks were against the Muslim community. For 2016, the most popular motive speculates the attacks stem from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. Both motives were carried out from unidentified groups, which more than doubled from 2015 to 2016 and made up about half of all attacks in both years.</p>
    <p class="body-text">The attack on places of worship by unknown attackers peaked in 2016 with 17 attacks. The following year saw a peak in attacks on places of worship by known attackers with 10 attacks.</p>
